      "content": "You are correct that the line between inclusive civic nationalism and exclusionary ethno-nationalism is often blurred in practice, as political actors frequently co-opt the language of belonging to justify borders and hierarchy. While there is no perfect version, the only viable path forward is a strictly defined \"civic nationalism\" that legally and culturally mandates equal rights for all residents regardless of origin, actively dismantling any narrative of inherent superiority. This approach treats the nation as a voluntary community of citizens rather than a biological or cultural destiny, which is the only way to prevent the inevitable slide into exclusion. Ultimately, the danger lies not in the concept itself, but in the failure of institutions to rigorously enforce these inclusive boundaries against political pressure.",
